-- Brazil Lawmakers Studying Ways to Curb Job Losses, Estado Says
-- B y   M a t t h e w   M a l i n o w s k i
-- 2012-10-07T15:16:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-07/brazil-lawmakers-studying-ways-to-curb-job-losses-estado-says.html
Brazil ’s government is considering
new measures aimed at curbing job losses nationwide, O Estado de
Sao Paulo reported.  Lawmakers aim to reduce unjustified firings and
unemployment benefit fraud, the newspaper said, citing
government officials. They’re weighing taxes on companies that
fire more workers than their competitors and tougher standards
for accessing  unemployment benefits , the publication said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Matthew Malinowski in Santiago at 
